
// This Hyperlambda code checks if a specified email template file exists using [io.file.exists]. If the file does not exist, indicated by the [not] slot, it logs an error message with [log.error] and returns a boolean false with [return-value]. This ensures that an error is logged and a false value is returned if the template file is missing.
if
   not
      io.file.exists:x:@.arguments/*/template-file
   .lambda
      log.error:Email template not found while trying to send template email
         template:x:@.arguments/*/template-file
      return-value:bool:false
